The paper discusses the use of deep learning in the automotive industry, specifically in the context of advanced driver assistance systems (ADAS) and autonomous driving. This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories, as these are the primary areas of focus for deep learning in the automotive industry. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and software engineering (cs.SE) categories, as these areas are also relevant to the development and deployment of ADAS and autonomous driving systems.
